Definition: large and economically important family of herbs or shrubs or trees often strongly scented and sometimes narcotic or poisonous
Example: includes the genera Solanum, Atropa, Brugmansia, Capsicum, Datura, Hyoscyamus, Lycopersicon, Nicotiana, Petunia, Physalis, and Solandra
Synonyms: adj, pert, solanaceous, family_Solanaceae, potato_family, asterid_dicot_family, order_Polemoniales, m, large, and, economically, important, family, of, herbs, or, shrubs, trees, often, strongly, scented, sometimes, narcotic, poisonous, includes, the, genera, Solanum, Atropa, Brugmansia, Capsicum, Datura, Hyoscyamus, Lycopersicon, Nicotiana, Petunia, Physalis, Solandra
Category: noun.plant
